## Metadata Requirements

All pages in the `app/` directory **MUST** export a `metadata` object, except for:
- `app/profile` - User profile page (excluded)
- `app/sso-callback` - SSO callback page (excluded)


### Required Metadata Fields

All page metadata objects must include all required fields. The metadata structure should follow this pattern:

#### TDK Character Limits

**CRITICAL**: All TDK (Title, Description, Keywords) fields must comply with character limits:

- **Title (T)**: ≤ 60 characters
- **Description (D)**: ≤ 160 characters  
- **Keywords (K)**: < 100 characters (total length of all keywords combined, separated by commas)

```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: string,                    // Page title (≤ 60 characters)
  description: string,              // Page description (≤ 160 characters)
  keywords: string[],               // SEO keywords array (total < 100 characters)
  robots: {
    index: boolean,
    follow: boolean,
    googleBot: {
      index: boolean,
      follow: boolean,
      'max-video-preview': number,
      'max-image-preview': string,
      'max-snippet': number,
    },
  },
  alternates: {
    canonical: string,              // Canonical URL
  },
  openGraph: {
    title: string,
    description: string,
    url: string,
    siteName: string,
    images: Array<{
      url: string,                    // Use `${siteUrl}/share-img.png` for default share image
      width: number,
      height: number,
      alt: string,
    }>,
    locale: string,
    type: string,
  },
  twitter: {
    card: string,
    site: string,
    title: string,
    description: string,
    images: string[],                // Use `${siteUrl}/share-img.png` for default share image
  },
};
```

### Share Image Path

**IMPORTANT**: The default share image path for OpenGraph and Twitter cards should be:
- Path: `/share-img.png`
- Full URL: `${siteUrl}/share-img.png` (where `siteUrl` is imported from `@/website-config`)

### Validation Checklist

When creating or updating pages in `app/`, ensure:
- ✅ `metadata` is exported (except profile and sso-callback pages)
- ✅ All required metadata fields are present
- ✅ **Title length ≤ 60 characters** (check: `metadata.title.length <= 60`)
- ✅ **Description length ≤ 160 characters** (check: `metadata.description.length <= 160`)
- ✅ **Keywords total length < 100 characters** (check: `metadata.keywords.join(', ').length < 100`)
- ✅ **Share images use `/share-img.png` path** (default: `${siteUrl}/share-img.png`)
- ✅ Values are appropriate for the specific page
- ✅ URLs use the correct site URL (can use `siteUrl` from `@/website-config`)

## Component Library Priority

**CRITICAL**: Always prioritize using shadcn/ui components over custom implementations:

### shadcn/ui Components

**REQUIRED**: When a component exists in the shadcn/ui library, use it instead of creating custom components:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - Use shadcn components
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTrigger } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';

// ❌ Incorrect - Custom implementation when shadcn component exists
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500">Click me</button>
```

**Available shadcn/ui Components:**
- `Button` - Use instead of custom buttons
- `Dialog` / `Sheet` - Use instead of custom modals
- `Input` / `Textarea` - Use instead of custom form inputs
- `Card` - Use instead of custom card containers
- `DropdownMenu` - Use instead of custom dropdowns
- `Toast` / `Alert` - Use instead of custom notifications
- `Avatar` - Use instead of custom avatar components
- `Badge` - Use instead of custom badges
- `Checkbox` / `Radio` - Use instead of custom form controls
- And other components in `components/ui/` directory

**Rules:**
- ✅ Check `components/ui/` directory first before creating custom components
- ✅ Use shadcn components with theme-aware styling (they automatically use theme colors)
- ✅ Extend shadcn components when needed, don't replace them
- ✅ If a component doesn't exist in shadcn, create it following shadcn patterns
- ✅ Use `cn()` utility function to merge Tailwind classes with shadcn components

### Adding New shadcn Components

If you need a component that doesn't exist, add it using shadcn CLI:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

This ensures consistency with the existing component library and theme system.

## Image and Link Components

**CRITICAL**: All images and links in the project must use Next.js optimized components:

### Image Component

**REQUIRED**: Always use Next.js `Image` component instead of HTML `<img>` tag:

```typescript
import Image from 'next/image';

// ✅ Correct
<Image 
  src="/logo.png" 
  alt="Logo" 
  width={100} 
  height={100}
  loading="lazy"
/>

// ❌ Incorrect
<img src="/logo.png" alt="Logo" />
```

**Rules:**
- ✅ Always import `Image` from `next/image`
- ✅ Always provide `width` and `height` props (or use `fill` for responsive images)
- ✅ Always provide `alt` text for accessibility
- ✅ Use `loading="lazy"` for images below the fold
- ✅ Use `priority` prop for above-the-fold images (e.g., hero images)

### Link Component

**REQUIRED**: Always use Next.js `Link` component instead of HTML `<a>` tag for internal navigation:

```typescript
import Link from 'next/link';

// ✅ Correct
<Link href="/about" prefetch={false}>
  About Us
</Link>

// ❌ Incorrect
<a href="/about">About Us</a>
```

**Rules:**
- ✅ Always import `Link` from `next/link`
- ✅ **`prefetch` defaults to `false`** - Only set `prefetch={true}` when explicitly needed for critical navigation paths
- ✅ Use HTML `<a>` tag only for external links (with `target="_blank"` and `rel="noopener noreferrer"`)
- ✅ For external links, use: `<a href="https://external.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">`

### Validation Checklist

When using images and links:
- ✅ All images use `Image` component from `next/image`
- ✅ All internal links use `Link` component from `next/link`
- ✅ **`prefetch={false}` is the default** (only set `prefetch={true}` when necessary)
- ✅ External links use `<a>` tag with proper security attributes
- ✅ All images have `alt` text for accessibility
- ✅ All images have explicit `width` and `height` (or use `fill`)
